This is what one year can do to you ♥️💯 

One year of consistency, hard work and determination. 
So exactly last year, around this time I started posting content on Instagram. 
I was fresh out of Masterchef and had around 20k followers.
Never in my life I imagined that one year later I’ll be almost touching 300k on Instagram and with a Silver Play Button in my hand. 

This is your sign to do what you love, follow your passion and to never fit in a box. 

Comment below and let me know what defines you? 🫶🏻

latestPosts.caption:
The most requested recipe is here !!!! HOMEMADE PROTEIN POWDER 

RECIPE- 
Pumpkin Seeds - 1/2 cup (12 grams) 
Chia seeds - 3/4 cup (40 grams) 
Flax Seeds - 1 cup (65 grams) 
Almonds - 1/2 cup ( 14 grams) 
Cocoa Powder -1/4 cup (5 grams) 

Add 2 big tablespoons of this powder in any of your favourite dessert or smoothie and it will work as a meal replacement. 

Serving size (2 tbsp) - 10 grams of protein 

This protein powder is not a replacement for your store-bought protein. 
This is an alternative that can be easily & safely consumed by growing children, teenagers and any adult who avoid consuming store bought protein. 
You can add this powder in porridges, milkshakes, home-made ice-creams, cakes, cookies etc.

Make this softest & fluffiest Instant Tandoori Kulcha at home using just a few ingredients and no resting time. 

Recipe-

Maida - 2 Cups
Sugar- 1 tsp 
Salt to taste 
Milk - 1/2 Cup
Dahi/ Curd - 1/2 Cup
Baking Powder - 1tsp
Baking Soda - 1tsp
Oil - 2tbsp
Boiled potato - 3 tbsp (mashed) 
Knead this to a soft dough,and let this rest for 15-20 mins. 
Then using minimal flour, shape these and cook on a tawa ( use splash of water to make it stick) 
Invert the tawa and cook to get that charred colour which replicates the tandoor
Optionally garnish with Kalonji & Coriander Leaves
Finish it off with 
Ghee/Butter and enjoy

These are my ultimate High Protein,Yummy,Melt-in-Mouth Beetroot Patties and when served with this nutty thecha dip, you won’t be able to resist it

Recipe- 
For patties- 
2 cups boiled chickpeas 
1 cup boiled beetroot, grated 
1.5 tbsp ginger-green chilli paste
1/4 cup onion, finely chopped 
1/4 roasted besan
1/2 tsp garam masala 
1 tbsp chaat masala
Salt to taste 
Handful of fresh coriander 

For thecha dip- 
3 tbsp thecha 
1/2 cup paneer 
1/4 cup yogurt 
Salt to taste 

Garnish with some coriander, peanuts and enjoy

Once you try this healthier version of Cold Cocoa, you won’t make it any other way. 
It’s thick,decadent, silky smooth yet super nutritious. 

Recipe (Serves 2) -
4 pitted dates 
10 almonds(skin removed)
3 tbsp cocoa powder
3 tbsp dark chocolate 
1.5 cups hot milk 

Soak this for 30 mins, blend really well and serve chilled over ice

This is not your usual breakfast but trust me it’s 10x better.
Given the heat, blazing sun and also the as the hottest day of the year approaches this is something you should eat. 
This is Assam’s Special Poita Bhaat with Alloo Pitika. 

This uses fermented rice which obviously makes it good for your gut and also keeps your body cool during summers. 

RECIPE- 
For Poita Bhaat - 
1 cup Cooked rice , soaked in 2 cups water over night
1/4 cup Curd
2 tablespoon Onions , chopped
2 Green Chillies , finely chopped
1 tbsp coriander, chopped 
Salt , to taste

For Aloo Pitika- 

3 Potatoes (Boiled)
2 tbsp onions, chopped 
1 tablespoon Mustard oil
2 Green Chillies
2 tbsp coriander, chopped 
Salt , to taste

🤝💞

Weightloss Friendly Asian Cucumber Noodle Salad 😋♥️

These are super yum low Calorie and High Fibre Noodles !! 
A perfect summer recipe which takes hardly any time to prepare 

RECIPE - 
2 cucumbers, sliced like noodles 
2 tbsp sesame oil 
1 tsp black sesame seeds 
1 tsp white sesame seeds 
2 cloves garlic 
1 tbsp red chilli powder 
1 tbsp dark soy sauce 
Some crushed peanuts for topping

Try this super-refreshing Coconut Crush loaded with the goodness of Gond Katira and Basil seeds. 
It’s an ideal drink for this summers and can protect you against a heat stroke. 

Recipe (Serves 2-3) 
2 cups fresh coconut water 
3-4 tbsp coconut malai (freshly scrapped) 
1 tsp sugar, if required 
Blend this all together with a few ice cubes. 
Now in a glass add- 
1 tbsp soaked gond katira 
2 tbsp soaked basil seeds 
Some crushed ice 
The blended coconut drink 

Serve chilled and enjoy♥️
